  "prompt": "What is the nicest library at Columbia to work at?",
  "response": "Columbia University has several libraries, each with its own unique atmosphere and offerings. Among them, the **Butler Library** is often considered one of the most iconic and favored by students for studying. It features a grand reading room, a variety of study spaces, and a vast collection of resources. \n\nAnother popular choice is the **Avery Architectural and Fine Arts Library**, especially for students in the architecture or arts disciplines. It offers a quieter, more specialized environment.\n\nFor a more modern setting, the **Science and Engineering Library** may be appealing for those in the STEM fields, as it provides updated resources and collaborative spaces.\n\nUltimately, the \"nicest\" library can vary based on individual preferences regarding ambiance, available resources, and study environments. It's a good idea to visit a few and see which one feels the best for your study needs!",
